FBIS4-53851 "dreas100_c_94028" FBIS-EAS-94-100 Daily Report 22 May 1994 North Korea Potong River Project Anniversary Marked Potong River Project Anniversary Marked SK2205085894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0813 GMT 22 May 94 SK2205085894 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, May 22 (KCNA) -- Working people here significantly marked the lapse of 48 years since the great leader President Kim Il-song participated in the ground-breaking ceremony of the Potong River improvement project and kindled the first flame of grand nature-harnessing . On May 21, 1946, President Kim Il-song initiated the Potong River improvement project as the first undertaking for carrying into practice the plan of land administration he had matured in the period of the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle, and took up the first spade at the ceremony. The project was completed in only 55 days thanks to the wise guidance of President Kim Il-song and to the great zeal and will of builders and Pyongyang citizens to build the country. With a view to conveying down through generations the immortal feat of President Kim Il-song, the Workers' Party and people of Korea set up a monument to the Potong River improvement project on the spot and annually celebrate May 21 as "day of builders". A meeting of working people in the capital city took place in front of the monument on May 21.
